sentences: Paria was an American, experimental metal band formed in 2001 and based in Omaha, Nebraska.
They went on indefinite hiatus in May 2010.
Paria formed in the fall of 2001 in Omaha, Nebraska.
The early stages of the band saw members come and go, but by 2003 a solid lineup materialized and the group began honing their sound.
On the strength of their EP, the band signed to Guy Kozowyk's Black Market Activities in March 2004 and began writing and recording their first full length album.
Misanthropos was released in November 2004, featuring the band's developed technical and experimental sound.
In the summer of 2005, vocalist Brian Craig and drummer Corey Barnes both left the band.
In early 2007, drummer Eric Schnee left the group to move back to New Jersey and reform his old band The Binding, while the band confirmed that Craig had "left the band for good" to finish college.
In June 2008, they sent the album to former vocalist Brian to see if he could guest on a few tracks.
The band released their second full length album The Barnacle Cordious in March 2009.

Paria formed in the fall of 2001 in Omaha, Nebraska.
The summer saw the band continue touring around the country, including a stop at the first annual Texas Murder Fest in Houston.
In the summer of 2005, vocalist Brian Craig and drummer Corey Barnes both left the band.
Because Craig had left the band to pursue college, he joined them on tour during the following summer when he was off from school.
On May 24, 2010, the band announced its "last show for an indefinite period of time" on June 5.
